Open Systems Interconnnection(OSI) model: It is a 7 layer framwork standardizing computer network communications, 
  moving from user interface (Layer 7) down to physical cables (Layer 1).  
7. Application: User interface (HTTP, FTP)
6. Presentation: Data encryption, formatting and compression.
5. Session: Manages user session and authentication.
4. Transport: End to end communication, flow control (TCP).
3. Network: Routing and logical addressing (IP).
2. Data link: MAC addressing and error correction.
1. Physical: Raw data transmission (cables, electricity)

Application layer:
Client-Server protocol: HTTP, FTP, SMTP, Web-socket(server can also talk to client, used for messaging apps)
Peer to Peer: Web RTC

CAP Theorem: Desirable property of distributed systems with replicated data.
  - Consistency, Availability, Parition tolerance.
  - CA, CP, AP are possible
  - CAP is not possible, because you cannot have a partition breakage and assure consistency and availability both.

